The paper deals with compressed sensing and spectral estimation, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The proposed sampling scheme is deterministic and simple, which suggests that it may fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SP) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a multitask algorithm based on variational Bayesian inference, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) or multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper focuses on frequency-sparse signals, which could be related to sparse signal processing (cs.SI).
